ranking college sg concerts for students week  (as a ?? na tatlo inattendan – pray for my wallet) and i hope walang ma-offend this is just a random persons expi
#1: kaleidoscope (cicssg) - sobra sobrang sobrang sobrang sulit lalo na for a student gov na bagong college lang (or bagong hiwalay?) nakakagulat talaga yung amount of booths na nagbebenta ng mga anik-anik whatever doon super naubos ang money + the lineup and the vibes were so good! 9/10 din yung mga inflatables nila! would be more fun if mas marami variety but goods na din !! overall i rate it a 10/10
#2: clachella (clacsg) - despite yung nakakaurat na ulan nagawa nila ang role nilang pagheheal ng inner child ng mga attendees nila (s/o sa mga chikiting sa naglaro sa ulan sana all !! ang cucute nio), andami din inflatables na natry tapos iba iba pa (pinaka bet ko yung nagtatalbugan kami ang laughtrip lang). na-discover ko din yung ajaa dito and OFC yung performance ng over october ay super solid din. 9/10 (9.5/10 kung di umulan) 
#3 Reverie/Chroma Blast (ceatsg): ngl i expected sm more from ceat given na isa sila sa pinaka-malaki ang budget. ang solid solid ng lineup though, i'll give them that yung performance ni zild ay pinaka-worth it na part ng concert. pero, kulang na kulang kami sa booths at inflatables. masaya din naman yung basaan concept pero nung bandang palubog na araw na medyo sinisipon na din dahil sa lamig HAHAHAHA so personally, it's a 7.5/10 for me (buhat ni zild)

I just confessed to my crush during SOLFEST 2024 na I like him. Also, I don’t mind if he rejects me or not pero ayun wala siyang sagot. So, expected ko na rejected me, then all of a sudden, Nag tanong siya na “huh? Ano yun?” HAYU* DI PALA NAKIKINIG SA SINASABI KO HAHAHAHAHA BUSY KASI SIYA KAY MOTHER DENISE I THINK PANGET TIMING. Right? But tbh din Denise was so beautiful like nakaka bakla siya mga ate. Ayun, back to him. He still rejected me pero ok na yun, after the concert nag dinner kami ng dalawa lang. and hinatid niya rin ako sa house namin, since commute lang naman ako and delikado na bumiyahe ng ganung oras so he initiated that night. I got shocked na after I confessed mas naging gentleman siya. That’s all for today.

My biggest takeaway from CEAT SG's Solfest is the lack of accountability. They didn’t even release a statement apologizing for the inconveniences they caused or reply to some comments and concerns. CEAT SG, remember that this event wasn’t only for the students of lasalle, you opened this to the public, and tickets were expensive so OBVIOUSLY EXPECTATIONS WERE HIGH! The way you handled your event was so unprofessional, tapos kunwari unbothered kayo?
Solfest was complete chaos. Imagine selling your tickets before the lineup was even released?! Selling VVIP Seated Tickets while having no concrete plan about how you would execute the VVIP Sections? The number of VVIP seats reached such a high because you kept accepting registrations without limitation!
Everything was released last minute—the seat plan, the full lineup, everything! It was only convenient for all the CEAT SG members, their families, and friends, who didn’t pay for anything but had better view than those who paid.
Bottom line, CEAT SG is a group of students who are unprofessional in their work and do not take action or accountability for people’s concerns. Up until now, from before the event to the day it happened, all you have caused is stress, inconvenience, and we have not received any apology.

Kita mo talaga sa ceatsg na walang accountability e, nagturn off comments, nagdelete pa ng comments, walang public statement/apology pati masyadong reply sa mga concerns. Andami ninyong taong na-agrabyado tapos wala lang? 
Kaya mas maraming natuwa sa cbaasg bukod sa business students sila at alam nila how to handle big events like this, they know how to handle critism. Nabash din naman yung flaire last time pero after ng concert puro “thank you cbaasg” na yung mga comments. Sa ceat puro padin problema yung comments pano imbis na iaddress tinurn off comments o kaya dinelete. Hindi naman magiging possible ung event nyo kung walang attendees, kailangan nyo pa din kami kung gusto nyo maging successful yung solfest nyo.
Accept criticism and be accountable kung gusto nyong magkaroon nang marami pang solfest kung pinagpapatuloy nyo nyan for sure maraming madadala at hindi na aattend kahit maganda pa pasabog at line up nyo.
